:12:\"options_page\";s:8:\"operator\";s:2:\"==\";s:5:\"value\";s:22:\"theme-general-settings\";}}}s:8:\"position\";s:6:\"normal\";s:5:\"style\";s:7:\"default\";s:15:\"label_placement\";s:3:\"top\";s:21:\"instruction_placement\";s:5:\"label\";s:14:\"hide_on_screen\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}','Options: Theme Settings','options-theme-settings','publish','closed','closed','','group_5a6b3def0c15b','','','2018-02-27 16:23:08','2018-02-27 16:23:08','',0,'http://do.ready-for-feedback.com/561-media/first-responders-network/?post_type=acf-field-group&#038;p=28',0,'acf-field-group','',0),(29,4,'2018-01-26 14:49:33','2018-01-26 14:49:33','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When a modern day hero signs up to be a first responder, workers compensation is not their first thought. These men and women put their lives and well being at risk every day to protect their community and their country. Unfortunately, first responders have some of the most dangerous jobs out there. It may not be their first thought, but being covered by workers comp is a huge concern when you get hurt on the job. At the First Responders Network, we want to make sure all first responders are taken care, just like they take care of the rest of us.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Getting Injured on the Job</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The high risks of working as a first responder means not wondering if, but when you will get hurt, how bad will it be, and how will you get treatment. Any injury that happens to you while on the job should be covered by your Workers Comp Insurance. If you experience any resistance, delays, or other troubles in getting the treatment you need an deserve, do not hesitate to contact the First Responders Network. We have a network of volunteers, lawyers, doctors, and other support to make sure you get the treatment you deserve. First responders are experts in saving lives, First Responders Network has the experts to support you.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>The Heart and Lung Bill</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you or someone you know is a first responder who has suffered from injuries or health complications caused by tuberculosis, heart disease, or hypertension from a work incident, then they may be covered by the Florida Heart and Lung Bill. It is vital that you understand your rights under this bill, because the application process for workers comp is different and there are certain requirements that must be met. If you qualify, you will be eligible for benefits to help pay for your medical care, treatment, and lost wages under the Heart and Lung Bill.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Do I qualify for the Heart/Lung Bill?</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The statute gives police officers, firefighters and corrections officers a rebuttable presumption that their heart, blood pressure or TB condition was caused by their employment. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You must have been diagnosed with hypertension, heart disease, tuberculosis, or hepatitis. Heart disease, can include many conditions, including coronary artery disease, arrhythmias such as atrial fibrillation, cardiomyopathy and more. The presumption may also cover any conditions caused by hypertension or heart disease, such as hypertensive strokes.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You must have undergone a pre-employment physical that failed to reveal evidence of the condition</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Must have missed work due to your injury or disability.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you believe you meet the above criteria, then you are most likely eligible for assistance under the Heart and Lung Bill. If you are not sure if you qualify, or you need guidance in getting your benefits when you do qualify, our knowledgeable experts at First Responders Network are here to help you. Or, take our quiz to see if you qualify for assistance!</span>','Work Compensation','','publish','closed','closed','','work-compensation','','','2018-02-28 20:01:05','2018-02-28 20:01:05','',12,'http://do.ready-for-feedback.com/561-media/first-responders-network/?page_id=29',0,'page','',0),(30,4,'2018-01-26 14:49:33','2018-01-26 14:49:33','','Work Compensation','','inherit','closed','closed','','29-revision-v1','','','2018-01-26 14:49:33','2018-01-26 14:49:33','',29,'http://do.ready-for-feedback.com/561-media/first-responders-network/29-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(31,4,'2018-01-26 14:49:49','2018-01-26 14:49:49','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Family Planning is important for families of all types, but particularly for those of First Responders. We never want to think of the worst-case scenarios, but when it comes to being a first responder, you and your family have to be prepared for anything. In the wake of a tragic event, there will be a lot to do. If you are hurt or killed, your loved ones will be heartbroken and overwhelmed with everything that needs to be taken care of. As a First Responder, you can take care of your family now by setting up a plan and thinking ahead. FRN is here to support any questions or concerns you may have.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Family Planning Checklist</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sign up for life insurance</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Name an executor of your estate</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Set up trusts for your children</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Draft a will and medical directive</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Have the tough discussions with your spouse</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Contact First Responders Network with your spouse</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Living with a Disability</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you as a first responder suffer injuries that lead to disability, there is coverage and laws in place to make sure you and your family are taken care of. See out other service pages on additional benefits and coverage. If the injury was caused at work, then workers compensation should cover any medical bills and lost wages. However, being a police officer, firefighter, or corrections officer is hard work and takes a toll on your body. Although disability insurance is not required in all states, like Florida, it is recommended. In the event that you become disabled from a non-work-related injury, your disability insurance will cover your lost wages.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>The Heart and Lung Bill</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you have suffered a work-related injury, your family should not have to worry. The Florida Heart and Lung Bill provide legal protection to eligible first responders. This protection ensures first responders and their families are covered in the event that they are disabled from heart disease, hypertension, or tuberculosis.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Do I qualify for Assistance Under the Heart/Lung Bill?</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The statute gives police officers, firefighters and corrections officers a rebuttable presumption that their heart, blood pressure or TB condition was caused by their employment. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You must have been diagnosed with hypertension, heart disease, tuberculosis, or hepatitis. Heart disease, can include many conditions, including coronary artery disease, arrhythmias such as atrial fibrillation, cardiomyopathy and more. The presumption may also cover any conditions caused by hypertension or heart disease, such as hypertensive strokes.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You must have undergone a pre-employment physical that failed to reveal evidence of the condition</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Must have missed work due to your injury or disability.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Life Insurance</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The loss of a loved one is one of the most difficult struggles anyone could ever face. We often rely on our spouses for support emotionally, physically, and financially. Replacing the emotional and physical support will not come easily. However, having a life insurance policy in place will make sure that your family is taken care of financially if you are no longer there for them.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Never think you are too young to have a plan for yourself or your family. First Responders are too likely to be struck by tragedy to not have a plan and to not know their resources. Both you and your spouse can use our network for lawyers, doctor, psychiatrists and more to help your family quickly get back on their feet in the event you are injured or killed in the line of duty. When it comes to family planning, First Responders Network is here to help! </span>','Family Planning','','publish','closed','closed','','family-planning','','','2018-02-28 20:01:10','2018-02-28 20:01:10','',12,'http://do.ready-for-feedback.com/561-media/first-responders-network/?page_id=31',0,'page','',0),(32,4,'2018-01-26 14:49:49','2018-01-26 14:49:49','','Family Planning','','inherit','closed','closed','','31-revision-v1','','','2018-01-26 14:49:49','2018-01-26 14:49:49','',31,'http://do.ready-for-feedback.com/561-media/first-responders-network/31-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(33,4,'2018-01-26 14:50:06','2018-01-26 14:50:06','Lorem ipsum dolor 