dd to their repertoire. These updated certification and training courses enable first responders to be effective at their position, so they may assist those in emergency situations. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Training resources come in a variety of ways such as classes, books and manuals, and online materials. These materials, however, can be abundant and may not apply to all first responders. Additionally, training materials and classes may be difficult to retrieve and schedule depending on the first responders dynamic schedule. Depending if you are a police officer, firefighter, or corrections officer, the training resources available may not apply to all first responder professions. At First Responders Network, we provide guidance to those looking to refresh their skills and learn new ones. Here are some of the training benefits and courses available. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Police Officers</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> - Courses and certifications are available for Basic crisis entry, Bomb threat safety, Active shooter response.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Firefighters -</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Courses and certifications are available for HAZMAT response, Emergency treatment, and Safety courses.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Corrections Officers</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> - Courses and certifications are available for G-license firearms certification, First-aid response, Defensive Tactics, and self-defense.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Heart and Lung Bill:</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First Responders can suffer from work-related injuries that can put stress on them and their families. The Florida Heart and Lung Bill can provide legal protection to first responders that qualify. This coverage ensures first responders and their families are protected in the event of disability from heart disease, hypertension, or tuberculosis.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The statute gives police officers, firefighters and corrections officers a rebuttable presumption that their heart, blood pressure or TB condition was caused by their employment. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A physician must diagnose you with hypertension, heart disease, tuberculosis in order to qualify for the Heart and Lung Bill. The presumption may also cover any conditions caused by hypertension or heart disease.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You have the option to seek a second opinion if medical conditions such as hypertension heart disease, or TB are caused by employment.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Families of first responders may qualify for coverage of medical expenses under the Hearth and Lung Bill.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Having direction on where you can receive training resources is an asset to improving your role as a first responder. Given the difficulty and risk of the job, programs such as the Heart and Lung Bill are in place to assist with work-related injuries for first responders. If you believe your health has been affected by employment, or not sure if you qualify for health-related benefits, let First Responders Network help you. Our team of professionals can walk you through the intricacies of the Heart and Lung Bill. Let First Responders Network be your training and resource center! </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Training and Resources','','publish','closed','closed','','training-and-resources','','','2018-03-01 14:23:35','2018-03-01 14:23:35','',12,'http://do.ready-for-feedback.com/561-media/first-responders-network/?page_id=35',0,'page','',0),(36,4,'2018-01-26 14:50:21','2018-01-26 14:50:21','','Training and Resources','','inherit','closed','closed','','35-revision-v1','','','2018-01-26 14:50:21','2018-01-26 14:50:21','',35,'http://do.ready-for-feedback.com/561-media/first-responders-network/35-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(37,4,'2018-01-26 14:50:37','2018-01-26 14:50:37','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First Responders Network provides assistance for those seeking to become a first responder and can provide recommendations for ongoing educational courses to keep your skills up to code with the latest laws in every state. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Emergency Medical Responders also known as, </span><b>certified first responders</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> are the earliest healthcare workers to arrive at an accident or scene of a medical emergency. As a crucial part of the emergency medical assistance team, a first responder quickly assesses emergency situations, calls an ambulance, and administers first aid. They must be able to remain calm in the midst of life-or-death crisis situations.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Becoming a certified first responder requires a high school diploma or GED, completion of training classes, and certification. The following steps below must be followed in order to become a first responder. Contact FRN today, if you need help with your states rules and regulations. </span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Step 1: Obtain CPR Training</span></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First responders are required to have certification in CPR for healthcare providers. Training and certification are found through the National Institutes of Health, the American Heart Association, and other venues.</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Step 2: Complete a State-Approved First Responder Course</span></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The U.S. Department of Transportation First Responder National Standard Curriculum is the standard for first responder training. To really stand out, take classes in anatomy and similar disciplines. A knowledge of human anatomy and physiology will help with understanding the skills needed as a first responder.</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Step 3: Take the Certification Exam for Career Advancement</span></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The National Registry of Emergency Medical Technicians (NREMT) offers certification and recertification to first responders. Applicants must pass cognitive and psychomotor examinations, which are taken through a state licensing agency and the NREMT.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First Responders Network can help assist in becoming a first responder while advising on additional courses that may be needed to maintain your license and credentials. If you have any questions on how to become a first responder we have a team of experts available to answer any questions you may have. </span>','Education','','publish','closed','closed','','education','','','2018-02-28 19:56:09','2018-02-28 19:56:09','',12,'http://do.ready-for-feedback.com/561-media/first-responders-network/?page_id=37',0,'page','',0),(38,4,'2018-01-26 14:50:37','2018-01-26 14:50:37','','Education','','inherit','closed','closed','','37-revision-v1','','','2018-01-26 14:50:37','2018-01-26 14:50:37','',37,'http://do.ready-for-feedback.com/561-media/first-responders-network/37-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(39,4,'2018-01-26 14:50:51','2018-01-26 14:50:51','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>First responders</strong> play a critical role in keeping our communities safe, and all Floridians benefit greatly from the services they provide. Our top priority at First Responders Network is keeping those who protect us safe and educated. We at First Responders Network understand the stress, constant exposure to trauma, life-threatening situations, and the physical strain of working long hours on little to no sleep can negatively impact overall mental health, increasing the vulnerability and risk of substance abuse and addiction among firefighters and first responders.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">FRN is here to help you find balance when the negative issues begin to outweigh the positive. Our team of experts can provide additional information about Health Benefits and coverage to make sure you are maintaining optimum mental health.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Understanding </span><b>YOUR RIGHTS!</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Florida Statute 112.18, commonly referred to as the Heart and Lung Bill. This policy was designed to offer added legal protection for police, fireman and correctional officers who suffer from heart disease, high blood pressure or tuberculosis from being injured on the job. The Heart and Lung Bill went into effect in Florida in 2002. </span>\r\n\r\n<b>Do I qualify for the Heart/Lung Bill?</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The statute gives police, firefighters and corrections officers a rebuttable presumption that their heart, blood pressure or TB condition was caused by their employment. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Must have been diagnosed with hypertension or heart disease.Heart disease can include many conditions, including coronary artery disease, arrhythmias such as atrial fibrillation, cardiomyopathy and more. The presumption may also cover any conditions caused by hypertension or heart disease, such as hypertensive strokes.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Must have undergone a pre-employment physical that failed to reveal evidence of the condition</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Must be disabled as a result of the condition.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Do you believe you may qualify for addition