";s:2:\"id\";s:0:\"\";}s:13:\"default_value\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"placeholder\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"maxlength\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"rows\";i:5;s:9:\"new_lines\";s:0:\"\";}','Ads script','ads_script','publish','closed','closed','','field_5a955f533e5f0','','','2018-02-27 13:41:56','2018-02-27 13:41:56','',219,'http://do.ready-for-feedback.com/561-media/first-responders-network/?post_type=acf-field&#038;p=280',0,'acf-field','',0),(281,3,'2018-02-27 15:17:16','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2018-02-27 15:17:16','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://do.ready-for-feedback.com/561-media/first-responders-network/?p=281',0,'post','',0),(282,3,'2018-02-28 19:55:47','2018-02-28 19:55:47','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First Responders Network provides assistance for those seeking to become a first responder and can provide recommendations for ongoing educational courses to keep your skills up to code with the latest laws in every state. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Emergency Medical Responders also known as, </span><b>certified first responders</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> are the earliest healthcare workers to arrive at an accident or scene of a medical emergency. As a crucial part of the emergency medical assistance team, a first responder quickly assesses emergency situations, calls an ambulance, and administers first aid. They must be able to remain calm in the midst of life-or-death crisis situations.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Becoming a certified first responder requires a high school diploma or GED, completion of training classes, and certification. The following steps below must be followed in order to become a first responder. Contact FRN today, if you need help with your states rules and regulations. </span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Step 1: Obtain CPR Training</span></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First responders are required to have certification in CPR for healthcare providers. Training and certification are found through the National Institutes of Health, the American Heart Association, and other venues.</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Step 2: Complete a State-Approved First Responder Course</span></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The U.S. Department of Transportation First Responder National Standard Curriculum is the standard for first responder training. To really stand out, take classes in anatomy and similar disciplines. A knowledge of human anatomy and physiology will help with understanding the skills needed as a first responder.</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Step 3: Take the Certification Exam for Career Advancement</span></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The National Registry of Emergency Medical Technicians (NREMT) offers certification and recertification to first responders. Applicants must pass cognitive and psychomotor examinations, which are taken through a state licensing agency and the NREMT.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First Responders Network can help assist in becoming a first responder while advising on additional courses that may be needed to maintain your license and credentials. If you have any questions on how to become a first responder we have a team of experts available to answer any questions you may have. </span>','Education','','inherit','closed','closed','','37-autosave-v1','','','2018-02-28 19:55:47','2018-02-28 19:55:47','',37,'http://do.ready-for-feedback.com/561-media/first-responders-network/37-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(283,3,'2018-02-28 19:56:09','2018-02-28 19:56:09','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First Responders Network provides assistance for those seeking to become a first responder and can provide recommendations for ongoing educational courses to keep your skills up to code with the latest laws in every state. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Emergency Medical Responders also known as, </span><b>certified first responders</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> are the earliest healthcare workers to arrive at an accident or scene of a medical emergency. As a crucial part of the emergency medical assistance team, a first responder quickly assesses emergency situations, calls an ambulance, and administers first aid. They must be able to remain calm in the midst of life-or-death crisis situations.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Becoming a certified first responder requires a high school diploma or GED, completion of training classes, and certification. The following steps below must be followed in order to become a first responder. Contact FRN today, if you need help with your states rules and regulations. </span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Step 1: Obtain CPR Training</span></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First responders are required to have certification in CPR for healthcare providers. Training and certification are found through the National Institutes of Health, the American Heart Association, and other venues.</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Step 2: Complete a State-Approved First Responder Course</span></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The U.S. Department of Transportation First Responder National Standard Curriculum is the standard for first responder training. To really stand out, take classes in anatomy and similar disciplines. A knowledge of human anatomy and physiology will help with understanding the skills needed as a first responder.</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Step 3: Take the Certification Exam for Career Advancement</span></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The National Registry of Emergency Medical Technicians (NREMT) offers certification and recertification to first responders. Applicants must pass cognitive and psychomotor examinations, which are taken through a state licensing agency and the NREMT.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First Responders Network can help assist in becoming a first responder while advising on additional courses that may be needed to maintain your license and credentials. If you have any questions on how to become a first responder we have a team of experts available to answer any questions you may have. </span>','Education','','inherit','closed','closed','','37-revision-v1','','','2018-02-28 19:56:09','2018-02-28 19:56:09','',37,'http://do.ready-for-feedback.com/561-media/first-responders-network/37-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(284,3,'2018-02-28 19:58:35','2018-02-28 19:58:35','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>First responders</strong> play a critical role in keeping our communities safe, and all Floridians benefit greatly from the services they provide. Our top priority at First Responders Network is keeping those who protect us safe and educated. We at First Responders Network understand the stress, constant exposure to trauma, life-threatening situations, and the physical strain of working long hours on little to no sleep can negatively impact overall mental health, increasing the vulnerability and risk of substance abuse and addiction among firefighters and first responders.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">FRN is here to help you find balance when the negative issues begin to outweigh the positive. Our team of experts can provide additional information about Health Benefits and coverage to make sure you are maintaining optimum mental health.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Understanding </span><b>YOUR RIGHTS!</b>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Florida Statute 112.18, commonly referred to as the Heart and Lung Bill. This policy was designed to offer added legal protection for police, fireman and correctional officers who suffer from heart disease, high blood pressure or tuberculosis from being injured on the job. The Heart and Lung Bill went into effect in Florida in 2002. </span>\n\n<b>Do I qualify for the Heart/Lung Bill?</b>\n<ul>\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The statute gives police, firefighters and corrections officers a rebuttable presumption that their heart, blood pressure or TB condition was caused by their employment. </span></li>\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Must have been diagnosed with hypertension or heart disease.Heart disease can include many conditions, including coronary artery disease, arrhythmias such as atrial fibrillation, cardiomyopathy and more. The presumption may also cover any conditions caused by hypertension or heart disease, such as hypertensive strokes.</span></li>\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Must have undergone a pre-employment physical that failed to reveal evidence of the condition</span></li>\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Must be disabled as a result of the condition.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Do you believe you may qualify for additional Health Benefits but, you are not sure where to start? Contact First Responders Network today or take our Quiz today. If you have questions pertaining to extended Health Benefits or other services offered by First Responders Network our Team of experts can help. </span>','Health Benefits','','inherit','closed','closed','','39-autosave-v1','','','2018-02-28 19:58:35','2018-02-28 19:58:35','',39,'http://do.ready-for-feedback.com/561-media/first-responders-network/39-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(285,3,'2018-02-28 19:58:41','2018-02-28 19:58:41','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>First responders</strong> play a critical role in keeping our communities safe, and all Floridians benefit greatly from the services they provide. Our top priority at First Responders Network is keeping those who protect us safe and educated. We at First Responders Network understand the stress, constant exposure to trauma, life-threatening situations, and the physical strain of working long hours on little to no sleep can negatively impact overall mental health, increasing the vulnerability and risk of substance abuse and addiction among firefighters and first responders.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">FRN is here to help you find balance when the negative issues begin to outweigh the positive. Our team of experts can provide additional information about Health Benefits and coverage to make sure you are maintaining optimum mental health.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Understanding </span><b>YOUR RIGHTS!</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Florida Statute 112.18, commonly referred to as the Heart and Lung Bill. This policy was designed to offer added legal protection for police, fireman and correctional officers who suffer from heart disease, high blood pressure or tuberculosis from being injured on the job. The Heart and Lung Bill went into effect in Florida in 2002. </span>\r\n\r\n<b>Do I qualify for the Heart/Lung Bill?</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The statute gives police, firefighters and corrections officers a rebuttable presumption that their heart, blood pressure or TB condition was caused by their employment. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Must have been diagnosed with hypertension or heart disease.Heart disease can include many conditions, including coronary artery disease, arrhythmias such as atrial fibrillation, cardiomyopathy and more. The presumption may also cover any conditions caused by hypertension or heart disease, such as hypertensive strokes.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Must have undergone a pre-employment physical that failed to reveal evidence of the condition</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Must be disabled as a result of the condition.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Do you believe you may qualify for additional Health Benefits but, you are not sure where to start? Contact First Responders Network today or take our Quiz today. If you have questions pertaining to extended Health Benefits or other services offered by First Responders Network our Team of experts can help. </span>','Health Benefits','','inherit','closed','closed','','39-revision-v1','','','2018-02-28 19:58:41','2018-02-28 19:58:41','',39,'http://do.ready-for-feedback.com/561-media/first-responders-network/39-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(286,3,'2018-02-28 20:00:15','2018-02-28 20:00:15','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Family Planning is important for families of all types, but particularly for those of First Responders. We never want to think of the worst-case scenarios, but when it comes to being a first responder, you and your family have to be prepared for anything. In the wake of a tragic event, there will be a lot to do. If you are hurt or killed, your loved ones will be heartbroken and overwhelmed with everything that needs to be taken care of. As a First Responder, you can take care of your family now by setting up a plan and thinking ahead. FRN is here to support any questions or concerns you may have.</span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>Family Planning Checklist</b>\n<ul>\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sign up for life insurance</span></li>\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Name an executor of your estate</span></li>\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Set up trusts for your children</span></li>\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Draft a will and medical directive</span></li>\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Have the tough discussions with your spouse</span></li>\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Contact First Responders Network with your spouse</span></li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>Living with a Disability</b>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you as a first responder suffer injuries that lead to disability, there is coverage and laws in place to make sure you and your family are taken care of. See out other service pages on additional benefits and coverage. If the injury was caused at work, then workers compensation should cover any medical bills and lost wages. However, being a police officer, firefighter, or corrections officer is hard work and takes a toll on your body. Although disability insurance is not required in all states, like Florida, it is recommended. In the event that you become disabled from a non-work-related injury, your disability insurance will cover your lost wages.</span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>The Heart and Lung Bill</b>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you have suffered a work-related injury, your family should not have to worry. The Florida Heart and Lung Bill provide legal protection to eligible first responders. This protection ensures first responders and their families are covered in the event that they are disabled from heart disease, hypertension, or tuberculosis.</span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>Do I qualify for Assistance Under the Heart/Lung Bill?</b>\n<ul>\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The statute gives police officers, firefighters and corrections officers a rebuttable presumption that their heart, blood pressure or TB condition was caused by their employment. </span></li>\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You must have been diagnosed with hypertension, heart disease, tuberculosis, or hepatitis. Heart disease, can include many conditions, including coronary artery disease, arrhythmias such as atrial fibrillation, cardiomyopathy and more. The presumption may also cover any conditions caused by hypertension or heart disease, such as hypertensive strokes.</span></li>\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You must have undergone a pre-employment physical that failed to reveal evidence of the condition</span></li>\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Must have missed work due to your injury or disability.</span></li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>Life Insurance</b>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The loss of a loved one is one of the most difficult struggles anyone could ever face. We often rely on our spouses for support emotionally, physically, and financially. Replacing the emotional and physical support will not come easily. However, having a life insurance policy in place will make sure that your family is taken care of financially if you are no longer there for them.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Never think you are too young to have a plan for yourself or your family. First Responders are too likely to be struck by tragedy to not have a plan and to not know their resources. Both you and your spouse can use our network for lawyers, doctor, psychiatrists and more to help your family quickly get back on their feet in the event you are injured or killed in the line of duty. When it comes to family planning, First Responders Network is here to help! </span>','Family Planning','','inherit','closed','closed','','31-autosave-v1','','','2018-02-28 20:00:15','2018-02-28 20:00:15','',31,'http://do.ready-for-feedback.com/561-media/first-responders-network/31-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(287,3,'2018-02-28 20:01:05','2018-02-28 20:01:05','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When a modern day hero signs up to be a first responder, workers compensation is not their first thought. These men and women put their lives and well being at risk every day to protect their community and their country. Unfortunately, first responders have some of the most dangerous jobs out there. It may not be their first thought, but being covered by workers comp is a huge concern when you get hurt on the job. At the First Responders Network, we want to make sure all first responders are taken care, just like they take care of the rest of us.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Getting Injured on the Job</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The high risks of working as a first responder means not wondering if, but when you will get hurt, how bad will it be, and how will you get treatment. Any injury that happens to you while on the job should be covered by your Workers Comp Insurance. If you experience any resistance, delays, or other troubles in getting the treatment you need an deserve, do not hesitate to contact the First Responders Network. We have a network of volunteers, lawyers, doctors, and other support to make sure you get the treatment you deserve. First responders are experts in saving lives, First Responders Network has the experts to support you.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>The Heart and Lung Bill</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you or someone you know is a first responder who has suffered from injuries or health complications caused by tuberculosis, heart disease, or hypertension from a work incident, then they may be covered by the Florida Heart and Lung Bill. It is vital that you understand your rights under this bill, because the application process for workers comp is different and there are certain requirements that must be met. If you qualify, you will be eligible for benefits to help pay for your medical care, treatment, and lost wages under the Heart and Lung Bill.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Do I qualify for the Heart/Lung Bill?</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The statute gives police officers, firefighters and corrections officers a rebuttable presumption that their heart, blood pressure or TB condition was caused by their employment. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You must have been diagnosed with hypertension, heart disease, tuberculosis, or hepatitis. Heart disease, can include many conditions, including coronary artery disease, arrhythmias such as atrial fibrillation, cardiomyopathy and more. The presumption may also cover any conditions caused by hypertension or heart disease, such as hypertensive strokes.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You must have undergone a pre-employment physical that failed to reveal evidence of the condition</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Must have missed work due to your injury or disability.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you believe you meet the above criteria, then you are most likely eligible for assistance under the Heart and Lung Bill. If you are not sure if you qualify, or you need guidance in getting your benefits when you do qualify, our knowledgeable experts at First Responders Network are here to help you. Or, take our quiz to see if you qualify for assistance!</span>','Work Compensation','','inherit','closed','closed','','29-revision-v1','','','2018-02-28 20:01:05','2018-02-28 20:01:05','',29,'http://do.ready-for-feedback.com/561-media/first-responders-network/29-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(288,3,'2018-02-28 20:01:10','2018-02-28 20:01:10','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Family Planning is important for families of all types, but particularly for those of First Responders. We never want to think of the worst-case scenarios, but when it comes to being a first responder, you and your family have to be prepared for anything. In the wake of a tragic event, there will be a lot to do. If you are hurt or killed, your loved ones will be heartbroken and overwhelmed with everything that needs to be taken care of. As a First Responder, you can take care of your family now by setting up a plan and thinking ahead. FRN is here to support any questions or concerns you may have.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Family Planning Checklist</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sign up for life insurance</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Name an executor of your estate</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Set up trusts for your children</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Draft a will and medical directive</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Have the tough discussions with your spouse</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Contact First Responders Network with your spouse</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Living with a Disability</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you as a first responder suffer injuries that lead to disability, there is coverage and laws in place to make sure you and your family are taken care of. See out other service pages on additional benefits and coverage. If the injury was caused at work, then workers compensation should cover any medical bills and lost wages. However, being a police officer, firefighter, or corrections officer is hard work and takes a toll on your body. Although disability insurance is not required in all states, like Florida, it is recommended. In the event that you become disabled from a non-work-related injury, your disability insurance will cover your lost wages.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>The Heart and Lung Bill</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you have suffered a work-related injury, your family should not have to worry. The Florida Heart and Lung Bill provide legal protection to eligible first responders. This protection ensures first responders and their families are covered in the event that they are disabled from heart disease, hypertension, or tuberculosis.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Do I qualify for Assistance Under the Heart/Lung Bill?</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The statute gives police officers, firefighters and corrections officers a rebuttable presumption that their heart, blood pressure or TB condition was caused by their employment. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You must have been diagnosed with hypertension, heart disease, tuberculosis, or hepatitis. Heart disease, can include many conditions, including coronary artery disease, arrhythmias such as atrial fibrillation, cardiomyopathy and more. The presumption may also cover any conditions caused by hypertension or heart disease, such as hypertensive strokes.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You must have undergone a pre-employment physical that failed to reveal evidence of the condition</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Must have missed work due to your injury or disability.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Life Insurance</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The loss of a loved one is one of the most difficult struggles anyone could ever face. We often rely on our spouses for support emotionally, physically, and financially. Replacing the emotional and physical support will not come easily. However, having a life insurance policy in place will make sure that your family is taken care of financially if you are no longer there for them.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Never think you are too young to have a plan for yourself or your family. First Responders are too likely to be struck by tragedy to not have a plan and to not know their resources. Both you and your spouse can use our network for lawyers, doctor, psychiatrists and more to help your family quickly get back on their feet in the event you are injured or killed in the line of duty. When it comes to family planning, First Responders Network is here to help! </span>','Family Planning','','inherit','closed','closed','','31-revision-v1','','','2018-02-28 20:01:10','2018-02-28 20:01:10','',31,'http://do.ready-for-feedback.com/561-media/first-responders-network/31-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(289,3,'2018-02-28 21:36:45','2018-02-28 21:36:45','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heeding the call for an emergency, first responders are essential for protecting and saving lives. The men and women who risk their lives go beyond the call of duty to ensure the safety of the public. A first responder serves their community by performing their high-risk occupation. In the line of duty, first responders can face injury and need medication to treat their wounds and physical ailments. When being injured on the job, first responders may not receive full treatment or pharmaceuticals through medical insurance or workers compensation. Not receiving the medication needed puts a physical strain on first responders, especially during the long hours they work. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First Responders Network understands the dedication and commitment of those individuals who answer the call. Our goal is to assist first responders by educating them on the facets of their workers compensation claims and health insurance, so they may receive the proper medical treatment. Insurance companies may only offer first responders partial or no medication. In some instances, the cost of medication at the pharmacy may be an exorbitant amount for first responders. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Pharmaceutical Treatment:</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Working a strenuous and physically demanding job asserts a tremendous amount of strain on the body. It can not only affect various muscle groups, but it can also be mentally stressful. The body becomes sore which causes aches and pains to develop. This makes it difficult for first responders to perform their duties, especially for those working in difficult conditions in Florida. Medicine is expensive especially for first responders whose insurance doesnt fully cover the cost. This is also true for first responders who file workers compensation claims after receiving an injury during work. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Thankfully, legislation in Florida has been passed to assist first responders with medical conditions such as hypertension, heart disease, or tuberculosis. Prescription medication for the treatment of these medical conditions can be a costly trip to the drugstore for first responders. Here are some of the benefits that first responders can qualify for from the Heart and Lung Bill.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Prescribed course of treatment</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> - means prescribed medicines for the specific disease or diseases claimed are compensated through the Heart and Lung Bill. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Independent medical examination</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> - In the event of a dispute in the appropriateness of prescribed medical treatment by the physician, an independent medical evaluation can be requested. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Qualification for prescribed course of treatment</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> - Your personal physician determines employment departure is caused by significant arrigrivation of hypertension, tuberculosis, and heart disease, then they will prescribe your treatment plan.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Workers Compensation</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> - Medical treatment through a workers compensation claim is determined if the employees departure was due to aggravated symptoms of heart disease, high blood pressure, and tuberculosis. Medications for these conditions are granted under the Heart and Lung Bill.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Researching your insurance policy or workers comp claim to see if you qualify for health benefits can be difficult. Having guidance sifting through the legalities of policies can leave you without receiving your full benefits. If you believe your health has been affected by work, but are unsure if you qualify for health-related benefits from the Heart and Lung Bill, let First Responders Network assist you. Our team of experts can walk you through the process and give you the information you need to make the best decisions for your health. </span>','Pharmacy','','inherit','closed','closed','','102-revision-v1','','','2018-02-28 21:36:45','2018-02-28 21:36:45','',102,'http://do.ready-for-feedback.com/561-media/first-responders-network/102-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(290,3,'2018-02-28 21:37:35','2018-02-28 21:37:35',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','290','','','2018-02-28 21:37:35','2018-02-28 21:37:35','',12,'http://do.ready-for-feedback.com/561-media/first-responders-network/?p=290',4,'nav_menu_item','',0),(291,3,'2018-03-01 14:23:35','2018-03-01 14:23:35','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First responders undergo extensive training and practice in order to provide effective and fast-acting service. Training and practice continue after passing certification and exams for first responders. Ongoing training is a key factor to keep abreast on the latest techniques and procedures. With the advancement of treatments and life-saving techniques, continuing training is essential for first responders. It can be the difference between life or death in an emergency situation.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First Responders Network understands the importance of the roles and duties first responders perform on a daily basis. We are dedicated to providing fellow first responders with the tools required to effectively perform their duties. We ensure first responders receive the information and resources needed to assist them with their jobs. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Training Resources:</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First responders training goes beyond educational courses and on-the-job training. There are certifications and updated training materials first responders can study to add to their repertoire. These updated certification and training courses enable first responders to be effective at their position, so they may assist those in emergency situations. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Training resources come in a variety of ways such as classes, books and manuals, and online materials. These materials, however, can be abundant and may not apply to all first responders. Additionally, training materials and classes may be difficult to retrieve and schedule depending on the first responders dynamic schedule. Depending if you are a police officer, firefighter, or corrections officer, the training resources available may not apply to all first responder professions. At First Responders Network, we provide guidance to those looking to refresh their skills and learn new ones. Here are some of the training benefits and courses available. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Police Officers</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> - Courses and certifications are available for Basic crisis entry, Bomb threat safety, Active shooter response.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Firefighters -</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Courses and certifications are available for HAZMAT response, Emergency treatment, and Safety courses.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Corrections Officers</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> - Courses and certifications are available for G-license firearms certification, First-aid response, Defensive Tactics, and self-defense.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Heart and Lung Bill:</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First Responders can suffer from work-related injuries that can put stress on them and their families. The Florida Heart and Lung Bill can provide legal protection to first responders that qualify. This coverage ensures first responders and their families are protected in the event of disability from heart disease, hypertension, or tuberculosis.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The statute gives police officers, firefighters and corrections officers a rebuttable presumption that their heart, blood pressure or TB condition was caused by their employment. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A physician must diagnose you with hypertension, heart disease, tuberculosis in order to qualify for the Heart and Lung Bill. The presumption may also cover any conditions caused by hypertension or heart disease.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You have the option to seek a second opinion if medical conditions such as hypertension heart disease, or TB are caused by employment.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Families of first responders may qualify for coverage of medical expenses under the Hearth and Lung Bill.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Having direction on where you can receive training resources is an asset to improving your role as a first responder. Given the difficulty and risk of the job, programs such as the Heart and Lung Bill are in place to assist with work-related injuries for first responders. If you believe your health has been affected by employment, or not sure if you qualify for health-related benefits, let First Responders Network help you. Our team of professionals can walk you through the intricacies of the Heart and Lung Bill. Let First Responders Network be your training and resource center! </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Training and Resources','','inherit','closed','closed','','35-revision-v1','','','2018-03-01 14:23:35','2018-03-01 14:23:35','',35,'http://do.ready-for-feedback.com/561-media/first-responders-network/35-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(292,4,'2018-03-05 16:30:47','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2018-03-05 16:30:47','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://do.ready-for-feedback.com/561-media/first-responders-network/?p=292',0,'post','',0);
